cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR

The paper deals with wireless communication networks for IoT devices, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-categories. The use of backscatter antennas and wireless energy transfer suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are likely sub-categories. The design of full-duplex communication and the use of time-hopping spread-spectrum indicate that cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MM (Multimedia) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the analysis of performance metrics such as bit-error rates and outage probabilities suggests that cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) could also be a relevant sub-category.
